    <text id="B0275T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>The firm of Crawford and Brother agree to settle a claim filed through the
                    Bureau.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Mr. <abbr expan="Thomas">Thos</abbr> P. Jackson</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-04-29"><orig reg="April">Aprile</orig> 29th <abbr expan="1867">/67</abbr></date>
                        <name type="place">Mount Alta <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Yours of the 20th inst. was received today &amp; we hast to reply - that we
                    will be pleased to settle the claim of George &amp; Abraham Simms by the
                    10th of May, or sooner if we can possibly do so. We assure you that the claim
                    will be met promptly by the 10th of May.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Your <abbr expan="Obedient">Obt</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Servants">Servts</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>Crawford &amp; <abbr expan="Brother">Bro.</abbr></signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">Address <abbr expan="Mount">Mt.</abbr> Alta P.O. Augusta
                            <abbr expan="County">Co</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
